I'm in this really bad never-ending circle right now. 3 years ago I lost around 20kg with intermittent fasting but I hit plateau and I'm stuck. 2 months ago I became so frustrated that I started this very strict diet and it only put my body in shock. I lose weight, eat a little more, gain weight, then want to lose weight again with very low calories, then gain weight again when I allow myself to eat normally again. My metabolism is now broken and so is my mental health around food especially. I booked a doctor appointment this upcoming Wednesday and hope they can help me fix my metabolism or even tell me if there's something wrong with my hormones or just anything since I still need to lose at least 10kg to get a healthy BMI. I'm so stuck and can't even look at food w/o thinking about how it's going to make me gain weight. I know I need to get in more calories to fix my metabolism so I can lose weight again but I get obsessed when I gain even by eating little more than usual and it make me so upset. The worse part is it's like I know what to do to fix the problem but I'm so stuck that it makes this whole situation not easy for me even though it should be easy. I hope someone can send some advice or even just a little encouragement </3

ive gained weight from 43kg to 85kg in 5 years. i stress eat, when i eat i ate a lot. like a lot bc i dont feel full. but when i dont eat, i didnt eat sometimes for a whole day. and i became a night owl. gaming and eating at 4am. so, since june, after my mom died, all i did was sleep and cry. not eating for 2 weeks, i drank only water. this month i scaled, 71.2kg. i was like hot damn, ive been failing to do diets because everytime i lose weight i became anxious. idk why. but whenever i lose some kgs, i would eat more. but now i lost 10kg?? so, ive decided to lose more and be healthy. waking up at 4am, going to work at 5am. on saturdays, i wake up at 7am, go to work at 8am. on sundays i rest. i tried working out after work but the pain is unbearable. so im not gonna do anything. just fixing the bad habit and eat 1 time a day. let's see if i can lose more weight after this.
